caption: Amazing food and service!!!!

Great ambiance, great service, but man is the food barely mediocre. How can you call your self a French restaurant and serve onion soup and escargot that are so bad? I feel terrible saying that, but the food is always so bland. Been about 8 times. I will go again inevitably, but that is only because I live next door. I wish so bad this place was good, you have no idea.

Visited 6 times in six months, and experience has been consistently great.  Staff is knowledgeable and attentive, food is amazing, and atmosphere is wonderful.  Although there isn’t a venue that can guarantee best experience, this one comes pretty close for me.

Food was seriously amazing. Very cute tucked in the corner of the building and inside is chill and dimly lit, nice ambiance for date night. I wouldn’t have expected the food to be so good but wow. Get the duck appetizer, mussels were amazing also. Loved the French onion soup, was the first time I’ve tried and probably won’t ever have one that compares to it now!
Trout almandine was delicious

Absolutely fantastic! Started with drinks: old fashioned and peach vodka - both excellent. Then had French onion soup (one of the best I've ever had) and Caesar salad (didn't really taste like a Caesar salad, very lemony, but still excellent. I had the burgony and pepper steak and frites- probably the best steak I have ever had. Seasoned beautifully and just melts in your mouth. Girlfriend had the seabass which she really liked. Shared a bottle of Bordeaux superior, which was nice. Finished the night with profiteroles. Decor and ambience were nice as well.
This restaurant is great and the food is very good.  The only reason it does not get 5 starts is that the selection is very limited and sometimes I cannot find something that I want on the menu.

What a lobby! Great classic French restaurant. It gets a loud and tight but that's how you know the place is good. I love their steaks. To me the au jus is a bit salty but I wash it down with a nice cocktail. Great for a date night in the heart of Lincoln Park.

It's COVID, so we should cut them dinner slack, but my experience wasn't great. Biggest issue is that the restaurant was absolutely frigid. We rushed just to be done.  Food and service were fairly good.

I told my friends about this place with my highest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The the food there is yummy and the team is generous and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we enjoy a gorgeous time.  warmly recommended.

We ordered from Mon Ami Gabi (still not comfortable eating out during the pandemic) and the meal was spectacular. The steak au poivre was heavenly, the salmon grilled to perfection, and both “survived” delivery really well. All the sides and accompaniments were great too!

Eating at Mon Ami Gabi during Christmas has been the tradition for four years and it never disappoints. Even this year we opt for take out option. One of best restaurants in Chicago and they know how to make delicious food.
Food was good as expected. Outdoor dining Is a little small so be sure to have a reso!
Great food great service.

Delicious Sunday afternoon meal.  Steak au poivre, with pommes frites.  Out of this world ... not bad for being in Lincoln Park along Chicago's lake front ... if we are In lockdown and cannot travel to France, perhaps we need to find the next best thing ...
French food... so good. There was fast and courteous service.
Upon arriving very cold host laid out rules. While I realize covid 19 is real as a customer I'm keeping this establishment open. I expect warm, friendly treatment when I arrive.

I have been going here since 2007 but I draw the line at receiving a bill “wet” and the waitress said “don’t worry, it is wet because of antiseptic. If either Mon Abi Gabi, Lettuce Entertain You, the GM or this particular waitress has COVID fear or issues; no prob, I get it. But I am not going back until I am comfortable. That was a real strange experience. Great chocolate and ambiance but no way I will go back when someone is literally spraying the receipt. Too bizarre for me. I think the Lettuce management should probably realize that those unique people who would appreciate that craziness do not go out... In shock. Even in these times we need common sense.

The service spectacular, this place is one of my favorite eats in Chi. This score is mainly because I feel my dish the Steak Frits was a bit extra salty and my parents shared the Coq ou Vin, and was also salty... but usually this place gets a 5star rate from me!
Great service and food in a historic Lincoln Park building.

Wow! This is the most delicious meal I have had in a long time. Merci for not taking the easy way out by reducing the shaved mozzarella, those delicate croutons, or (heaven help us) substituting iceberg 😢 on a Caesar salad! C’tait magnifique! The steak au poivre with frites...and the incredible French bread. You may be my new FAVORITE restaurant! Thank you - I am so happy to know that I can eat a slice of France in 2020 while at home in Chicago 🇫🇷 🧳 ♥️

My top place for quality french food. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. This place has a good feel to it. Similar to a place in Denver I liked.
One of my top locations for tasty french food. nothing but enjoyable experiences here. it has a great feel to it. ambience reminds me of san diego's scene.
Great scene for tasty French food. Had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again. The prices are well within reason for the quality.

Fantastic! Covid procedures in place.  Temp taking. The menu is limited so missing our FAVORITE Scallops 😩 but we soldiered on! We were outside on the patio which was terrific on a perfect 70° night. Great onion soup,  broke my diet and had some baguette totally worth it. Frisee Salad with warm cut bacon Yum! Duck Confit sooo good!  Steak Bordelaise was FULL of flavor. Topped the meal off with a taste of banana sorbet (nice banana flavor) and some kind of decadent double chocolate cake that was light and airy. Service was perfect.  Pro-tip if you sit outside don't let them put you at the table on top of the stairs. You end up in a parade of people.
french food and the scene at this spot is very good. Very savory. The service was very friendly and attentive. They have a lot of good reviews for a reason.
french food, mmm, super good. Came in on a Thurs. I'll return with my relatives. The prices are fair for the quality of food. Not close to my job, I wish it was.

Vache sacrée... not sure if that idiom translates, but flavor sure does.  We were blown away by the quality of the food, even delivered. Nestled inside the tony Belden Stratford is this delightful French restaurant.   Staff did a wonderful job despite all the hassles of dealing with Covid-19.   Service was impeccable,  at our own pace and not rushed.   Food was delicious,  well seasoned and we all had empty plates.
Awesome staff and outdoor space. Quality service, food, and wine. Would definitely come back!

the food is great...the service was extremely poor..we had hors d'œuvres entrees coffees deserts and drinks...then we did ask the waiter at the beginning about lettuce entertain and he said yes...at the end when we wanted him to add he said he could not informing us rudely that a table had 1hr45 min limit..)..after all the food and drinks we ordered you would expect the tell you..then we would hace ordered just an entree and one round of drinks to enjoy rather than rudely rushing us from the table . This was my first time experiencing Mon Ami Gabi despite countless recommendations of this must-try restaurant. Some consider it to be a french staple from the Lettuce Group, and I must agree. Everything here was delicious and everything coming out of the kitchen looked amazing. I would DEFINITELY recommend the steak frites. The strip steak is marbled, but perfectly trim for no far around the edges. A true work of art. The fries are super crispy as well. 10/10 for both.  To top it off the service was so stellar. Be careful, the bread is piping hot when they bring it to your table.  The restaurant does have a lot of tables inside, so there's not a lot of room between you and your neighbors, but the restaurant still isn't too loud. They strike the right balance.

I have celiac disease and Mon Ami Gabi was recommended to me as a place that has a nice selection of gluten free options. I LOVED my entire experience there. Went for one of the few brunch spots during restaurant week with a great group of friends. This French bistro is really on their gastronomy game and the space is very comfortable and quaint. I had the French onion soup, Lorraine omelette and the desert pictured which was delectable with warm chocolate syrup. Wow, as soon as you walk into Mon Ami Gabi you instantly sense that you are in a high-end restaurant. The restaurant is tucked right inside the Belsen Stratford Apartment building, I went with a group of friends on a Friday evening for dinner.  Each of us ordered different dishes so we could try everything else, but what we were really curious about were the escargot and the skate wing. The escargot was super delicious, it was covered in this garlic buttery sauce that tasted like pesto. After we polished off the escargot, we actually used the sauce it came in as a dipping sauce for our bread.  A skate wing is the wing of a stingray. I've never eaten stingray before so I didn't know what to expect. But as soon as I put a piece in my mouth and tasted that tender piece of meat I was blown away. It is hard to believe that this dish came from an animal that looks like it's made purely out of cartilage. Highly recommend!  All the other dishes were superb as well, but I highly recommend getting the above if you want to experience something new!

I had dinner there a few days ago.  We were greeted, seated promptly & bread, butter & water were brought to the table quickly.  After our meals were served, our waiter told us (didn't ask us, but told us!) that our food looked good.  She then left & we did not see her again until she brought us the check.  I ordered the Dover sole.  It was de-boned before it reached the table.  It was pretty mutilated, so if presentation is important to you, you may want to pass on this dish.  The fish had a nice crust, but the sauce left quite a bit to be desired.  It was not well-blended.  I ordered whipped potatoes and brussels sprouts as side dishes.  The sprouts were very good, but the potatoes were flavorless and runny.  My partner ordered the bouef bourguignon & it was a very hearty portion.  It didn't have as much bacon flavor as when I make it.  It was served on a bed of noodles.

I come to Chicago 2-4 times a year with friends and we enjoy taking our families to great restaurants around the city.  We had a group of seven and this was by far the worst service I’ve had in years.  Servers got food order wrong and the manager was rude about everything.  Considering the amount of money I spent I will never go to this chain again and would not recommend them to anyone I know.

Perfection! We were a little leery because they are so family friendly but we had a delightful evening even though we were surrounded by kids. The food was incredible! The Duck Confit was the best I have ever had. The Beef Tenderloin was delicious and the desserts were heavenly.

Our group was 8 in size. We had a reservation and arrived before 5pm, our reservation time, and the time they open (Sunday hours are 5-8:30pm).  We were taken to our table which was set for 6 people....not the end of the world.  Our server was friendly and ready to attend us.  She was advised we were not in a hurry.  She took our drink order, advised  us as to the specials and gave us time to peruse the menu before taking our order.  6 at the table ordered appetizers.  Before they arrive, the bread plates are removed (the bread and butter are still on the table) and all of the forks and knives are replaced (in a bit of a flurry).  I now have nothing to put my bread on.  The reviews were mixed on the appetizers. Once again there is a flurry of activity to clear the table of utensils and plates,  even those unused. While 2 people are still eating their appetizers, the dinner arrives at the table.  This is a major pet peeve of some of us at the table.  After all, this is fine dining.  The dinners were sent back to the kitchen to, most likely, sit under heat lamps.  We are being served at record speed. Dinner is now re-served.  One of the specials, halibut,  was what most of  us call appetizer size, about 3 1/2 inches by 1 1/2 inches in size all for $36.  2 people ordered that, it came with no sauce,  and 1 asked for some sauce because hers was very dry (could be the heat lamp situation caused that!).  I ordered the beef wellington.  It was cooked perfectly but I would have to say that the sauce was lacking flavor.  My husband was disappointed (taste and quantity) with his frites meal (steak with sauce) and said the frites were limp. The bright side of the evening was dessert.  No complaints from anyone, as a matter of fact, compliments all around. We passed some of them around so that all could get a taste. Not a great experience for my money and will never go back.
